sentences: Ronald Edward Cuber (born December 25, 1941) is a jazz saxophonist.
Cuber can be heard on Freeze Frame by the J. Geils Band, and one of his most spirited performances is on Dr. Lonnie Smith's 1970 Blue Note album Drives.
Cuber was in Marshall Brown's Newport Youth Band in 1959, where he switched from tenor to baritone sax.
His first notable work was with Slide Hampton (1962) and Maynard Ferguson (1963–1965).

He was also a member of the Lee Konitz nonet from 1977 to 1979.
